      "title": "Auth and Billing Migrations",
      "slug": "auth-billing-migrations",
      "shortDescription": "Migration of authentication system from AWS Cognito to Keycloak with Stripe billing integration. Building a trust service to synchronize user subscriptions and roles between both platforms.",
      "longDescription": "A comprehensive authentication and billing migration project aimed at modernizing the user management infrastructure. The system replaces the legacy AWS Cognito authentication with Keycloak for enhanced security and flexibility. A custom trust service acts as a bridge between Keycloak and Stripe, automatically synchronizing user subscriptions, payment status, and role assignments. The solution leverages Argo Workflows for orchestration, AWS SQS for message queuing, and Kubernetes for container orchestration. This ensures seamless user experience while maintaining data consistency across platforms. Built with Python, the service handles complex workflows including subscription lifecycle management, role-based access control, and real-time synchronization between identity and billing systems.",
